These girls are so special. Their spirits and their talents are unmatched. I was so excited to have a song on their last album, so I’m over the moon to have a song on the next collection of songs. 

“Work Of Heart” was a title I had in my phone for a long time. I’d thrown it out in a few writes and no one really took to it. Now I know why. Bobbi, Kyla, Brittni, and I sat down with their producer extraordinaire @anthonyfiddler and wrote the most moving song about the beauty in the ups and downs of life. And we wrote it during 2020 over Zoom when everything was really scary. 

Long story long, the pre-save link is in my bio and I can’t wait for y’all to hear this masterpiece. 💕

I loved these girls the moment I met them. (back in I think 2018?) I was thrilled to have a song on their “I Am” album. “Symptoms” is such an infectious jam. See what I did there..? 💕

The girls and I got on Zoom one day with their producer Anthony during the crazy heavy and scary times of 2020. I had “Work Of Heart” on my idea list for a long time. I’m not sure what inspired me to share it with them that day, but they ran with it. So much talent pours out of this group, I honestly just try and get out of the way! But it’s magical to watch. I hope you’ll all take a few minutes to add this song to your playlist. Anthony and the girls made this more than just a beautiful song, the track is an experience. 🌸

May this song remind you that the good, the bad, and the in between are all beautiful. It’s all a Work Of Heart ❤️

It’s been a busy time! I haven’t had much opportunity to post about this but I’m excited for it to be out. After so many years of releasing songs I had a hand in creating, I wanted to record a song I always loved but didn’t write. Difficult decision, right? “So Sick” by @neyo has always been a favorite. So with the help of the brilliant @parkerdanielguitar we made it happen. I hope y’all are diggin my little rendition. It ain’t blowin up on the TikTok or gettin tons of streams, but the vibes are good and it makes ya wanna turn the volume up, which I think is what counts. Thanks for listening, fam! 🩷

social_posts.post_text: Quite a group💙
Tis the season for believin’ ❤️🎄🎅🏼 #christmas #christmasmusic

Last night was a dream come true.✨

I have been a fan of @christmas4kidstn for many years. I’ve personally seen what they do. First hand. They don’t just give each kid a pair of socks. They throw these children a party. A massive party! Then they load them all onto buses and take them shopping. “Controlled chaos” Randy Oxley, VP of C4K calls it. Each child gets to spend $150. I’m told most the time, they spend the money on their loved ones. 

I always wanted to be invited to be a part of their tour bus event that happens in my hometown of Hendersonville, TN. I’ve gotten to do it a number of times now. It’s magical. But this year I wanted to do more. 

I called my friend @sarahbonsignore who’s thrown successful fund raising events in the past. I simply called for advice. She insisted on hosting. We spent weeks planning and it went off without a hitch. None of this would’ve been possible with Sarah. Another huge thank you to one of my best friends, Mr. @joelshewmake Thank you for saying yes every time I call. 

I am blessed beyond measure to have more incredible friends to call on. I must give a special shout out to Mike Reid, Kyle Lehning, and @marknarmoremusic for donating special items for the auction. 

Thank you to the angel in my life, Eryn Cooper @onairwitheryn and her team at @wsmradio who provided us with @opry concert tickets and @theryman tours. 

Together we raised over $1200. (Might be closer to 2k. It was my first benefit and to be honest I lost track.) 

Thanks for some of these great pics @caseybrynnlyrics 

Thank you everyone for showing up and believing in the magic of Christmas with me. It really is the most wonderful time of the year. 

Thank you for what you do @christmas4kidstn ❤️🎄🙏🏼
